WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.880 --> 00:00:11.050
I'm not drunk.

2
00:00:11.260 --> 00:00:12.640
I'm not drunk.

3
00:00:12.770 --> 00:00:14.750
-You're drunk.
-I'm not drunk.

4
00:00:14.980 --> 00:00:16.160
Really...

5
00:00:18.040 --> 00:00:20.770
Why drink so much
when you can't hold your liquor?

6
00:00:21.050 --> 00:00:22.000
Get some rest.

7
00:00:22.460 --> 00:00:23.270
Bye.

8
00:00:43.820 --> 00:00:46.440
Lee Gilyoung. the suspect
in the Kang Woosung murder case.

9
00:00:43.870 --> 00:00:48.770
[Breaking: Danhyeon "Casino Owner Murdered";
the suspect is his driver. Lee]

10
00:00:46.590 --> 00:00:48.140
-took his own life in prison
-Make way!

11
00:00:48.140 --> 00:00:50.840
before a final conviction
could be reached.

12
00:00:51.010 --> 00:00:52.670
Reports show that Lee's wife

13
00:00:52.910 --> 00:00:54.940
-passed away early.
-Get in.

14
00:00:55.060 --> 00:00:58.530
and he raised his son alone.
suffering severe financial hardship.

15
00:00:58.530 --> 00:00:59.770
According to the police.

16
00:00:59.770 --> 00:01:03.720
he was accused of murdering Kang Woosung.
his former classmate and employer.

17
00:01:03.720 --> 00:01:05.450
and stealing his valuables...

18
00:01:12.539 --> 00:01:14.140
119. what is your emergency?

19
00:01:15.150 --> 00:01:16.550
Where is your emergency?

20
00:01:21.890 --> 00:01:25.760
The amount he took was reportedly
a mere one million won (<$1.000).

21
00:01:26.650 --> 00:01:28.330
Lee's son asserts
his father's innocence...

22
00:01:28.330 --> 00:01:30.170
Son. come out. Let's eat.

23
00:01:31.670 --> 00:01:32.750
Dad.

24
00:01:42.890 --> 00:01:45.250
I prayed day after day.

25
00:01:45.950 --> 00:01:47.700
Death is too easy for him.

26
00:01:47.830 --> 00:01:48.840
He has to suffer;

27
00:01:49.910 --> 00:01:52.110
a living hell where he wishes for death.

28
00:01:54.320 --> 00:01:56.120
May you be hounded by cowardice.

29
00:01:56.220 --> 00:01:58.820
trapped in a life of misery
yet unable to end it.

30
00:02:02.350 --> 00:02:03.390
Just like me.

31
00:02:04.350 --> 00:02:05.340
[Kang Taeseon]

32
00:02:06.000 --> 00:02:07.610
[Certificate of appointment:
Ju Taeseon]

33
00:02:07.450 --> 00:02:10.380
I decided to bet my whole life
on locking up scum

34
00:02:10.630 --> 00:02:13.120
like Lee Gilyoung and his son.

35
00:02:14.110 --> 00:02:17.510
Ohsong Group's casino hotel bid
and Kang Woosung's murder

36
00:02:17.640 --> 00:02:18.890
are definitely linked.

37
00:02:18.890 --> 00:02:24.560
[Prosecutor Ju Taeseon]

38
00:02:19.860 --> 00:02:21.660
He might not be the real culprit.

39
00:02:21.890 --> 00:02:24.000
but that doesn't matter to me.

40
00:02:24.490 --> 00:02:26.110
Before I'm a prosecutor.

41
00:02:26.780 --> 00:02:29.370
I'm the son of Kang Woosung.
a victim of a brutal murder.

42
00:02:28.430 --> 00:02:29.450
[Kang Woosung (45. male)]
[Found dead at home; multiple stabs]

43
00:02:29.450 --> 00:02:30.380
[An awl found.
with Lee Gilyoung's DNA on it]

44
00:02:31.370 --> 00:02:32.530
That bastard who

45
00:02:32.730 --> 00:02:35.370
became a cop with his petty beliefs
deserves to be destroyed;

46
00:02:33.120 --> 00:02:34.390
[Lee Chaeha. Top Police Graduate:
"A World Where the Innocent Aren't Wronged"]

47
00:02:35.920 --> 00:02:37.380
destroyed by my own hands.

48
00:02:37.770 --> 00:02:38.860
And you...

49
00:02:40.540 --> 00:02:41.600
Hello. everyone.

50
00:02:41.780 --> 00:02:43.980
I'm Lee Chaeha. newly-appointed here.

51
00:02:47.780 --> 00:02:49.960
You actually came to me on your own.

52
00:02:55.600 --> 00:02:56.890
So shamelessly.

53
00:02:57.400 --> 00:02:59.120
as if nothing happened.

54
00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:04.280
[Park Siwoo]

55
00:03:06.800 --> 00:03:09.050
[Kim Yunsik]

56
00:03:14.520 --> 00:03:16.150
[Kwak Seunghwan:
because of property division?]

57
00:03:16.820 --> 00:03:18.390
[Kim (Koryoin): drug overdose]

58
00:03:18.590 --> 00:03:20.250
[Found in a small room
on the second floor]

59
00:03:20.460 --> 00:03:22.100
[Last abandoned mine in Danhyeon
to be converted into a casino...]

60
00:03:23.280 --> 00:03:25.270
[Danhyeon Land construction led by Ohsong:
casino. hotel. theme park. resort...]

61
00:03:25.490 --> 00:03:27.630
[First female executive
in the casino industry...]

62
00:03:27.630 --> 00:03:29.780
[Promises "transparent management
and regional win-win"]

63
00:03:29.980 --> 00:03:31.720
[Danhyeon City "Casino Owner Murdered";
the suspect is his driver. Lee]

64
00:03:38.200 --> 00:03:40.550
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

65
00:03:42.720 --> 00:03:44.170
Where are you going?

66
00:03:47.760 --> 00:03:49.800
But I miscalculated.

67
00:03:50.590 --> 00:03:51.820
You know what?

68
00:03:52.500 --> 00:03:55.200
No one would welcome a guy like you.

69
00:03:56.220 --> 00:03:58.740
How could anyone like you?

70
00:03:59.300 --> 00:04:01.140
So no matter what comes at you.

71
00:04:02.790 --> 00:04:04.530
you just have to take it.

72
00:04:05.840 --> 00:04:07.040
That day broke you.

73
00:04:07.390 --> 00:04:09.690
and you've remained broken ever since.

74
00:04:10.730 --> 00:04:11.730
Just like me.

75
00:04:11.990 --> 00:04:14.160
You're just using
my belief in my dad's innocence

76
00:04:14.160 --> 00:04:16.630
as a pawn to reach your goals. right?

77
00:04:17.089 --> 00:04:18.839
Is this what it means when you said

78
00:04:18.839 --> 00:04:20.380
I just have to take it?

79
00:04:20.940 --> 00:04:22.330
I don't know why.

80
00:04:23.030 --> 00:04:25.180
but seeing you suffer
wasn't satisfying at all.

81
00:04:25.180 --> 00:04:27.040
What do you know about my dad and me

82
00:04:27.060 --> 00:04:28.740
to rip open my wound like this?

83
00:04:29.260 --> 00:04:31.650
Who gave you the right to?

84
00:04:32.530 --> 00:04:33.780
It hurt.

85
00:04:35.140 --> 00:04:36.260
Lee Chaeha.

86
00:04:36.690 --> 00:04:38.490
I can only be so patient with you.

87
00:04:38.720 --> 00:04:39.670
Hope?

88
00:04:39.950 --> 00:04:42.690
Kill all hope.
Don't even entertain the thought.

89
00:04:42.980 --> 00:04:45.210
I need a competent investigator

90
00:04:45.530 --> 00:04:48.400
with a police background.
not an immature babbler.

91
00:04:48.409 --> 00:04:51.300
How can the perpetrator's kin
investigate the case justly?

92
00:04:51.300 --> 00:04:53.100
I'm staying out of it.

93
00:04:54.500 --> 00:04:55.510
Fine.

94
00:04:56.630 --> 00:04:59.000
I guess I'm the only one left

95
00:04:59.290 --> 00:05:00.840
who cares about the case.

96
00:05:01.160 --> 00:05:03.520
I really do need a partner
who's desperate for the truth;

97
00:05:03.520 --> 00:05:06.310
who will relentlessly pursue the truth.

98
00:05:06.630 --> 00:05:07.630
Why?

99
00:05:08.000 --> 00:05:10.650
Why are you so obsessed with this case?

100
00:05:11.740 --> 00:05:15.230
The truth.
Because I want the truth.

101
00:05:15.950 --> 00:05:17.650
What truth?

102
00:05:18.090 --> 00:05:20.690
To resent you and your father.

103
00:05:21.320 --> 00:05:25.880
I should at least be certain of the truth.

104
00:05:28.300 --> 00:05:30.030
Aren't you curious?

105
00:05:31.190 --> 00:05:33.040
Don't you want the truth?

106
00:05:33.310 --> 00:05:34.940
We both need the truth.

107
00:05:35.080 --> 00:05:36.220
me

108
00:05:36.350 --> 00:05:37.620
and Lee Chaeha.

109
00:05:38.120 --> 00:05:39.270
Because...

110
00:05:41.170 --> 00:05:43.600
What if the truth is more revolting?

111
00:05:45.870 --> 00:05:48.040
What if I can no longer

112
00:05:48.500 --> 00:05:51.210
love my father anymore?

113
00:05:51.560 --> 00:05:55.650
No matter how revolting it is.
at least you'll know the truth.

114
00:05:56.890 --> 00:06:01.300
You're still trapped in
the day your father killed someone.

115
00:06:01.880 --> 00:06:04.950
That's why you spend every moment
trying to prove that

116
00:06:05.150 --> 00:06:06.950
you're different from him.

117
00:06:07.710 --> 00:06:10.640
thinking you just have to
take whatever comes at you.

118
00:06:10.940 --> 00:06:12.590
This is the only way you and I.

119
00:06:12.870 --> 00:06:16.670
both trapped in that day.
can finally find peace.

120
00:06:17.390 --> 00:06:19.520
When you see the truth.

121
00:06:20.020 --> 00:06:21.770
you'll be able to move on.

122
00:06:22.270 --> 00:06:23.930
Let's investigate together.

123
00:06:24.060 --> 00:06:25.580
Let's uncover

124
00:06:26.300 --> 00:06:28.190
what the truth really is.

125
00:06:30.820 --> 00:06:34.909
Why do I want to become happy with you?

126
00:06:36.420 --> 00:06:38.320
Is it because you're the only one

127
00:06:39.060 --> 00:06:41.630
who share the same grief of that day as I?

128
00:06:55.180 --> 00:06:56.690
Stop crying and go home.

129
00:06:59.030 --> 00:07:00.280
See you tomorrow.

130
00:07:07.320 --> 00:07:09.970
[Prosecution]

131
00:07:26.470 --> 00:07:28.760
[Prosecutor Ju Taeseon]

132
00:07:38.420 --> 00:07:41.630
You're still trapped in
the day your father killed someone.

133
00:07:41.630 --> 00:07:44.190
That's why you spend every moment
trying to prove that

134
00:07:44.190 --> 00:07:45.720
you're different from him.

135
00:07:45.850 --> 00:07:47.510
Let's investigate together.

136
00:07:47.590 --> 00:07:49.140
Let's uncover

137
00:07:50.190 --> 00:07:52.050
what the truth really is.

138
00:07:58.520 --> 00:08:00.310
I'll be right there. OK.

139
00:08:02.580 --> 00:08:03.780
You... You're here.

140
00:08:06.070 --> 00:08:06.900
That's...

141
00:08:07.900 --> 00:08:08.910
Isn't that mine?

142
00:08:09.120 --> 00:08:11.550
Oh... this?

143
00:08:12.290 --> 00:08:13.810
This is yours!

144
00:08:15.890 --> 00:08:18.050
How should I put it? Wearing it.

145
00:08:18.210 --> 00:08:20.300
my hand feels warm. and...

146
00:08:20.860 --> 00:08:23.650
I thought it might
make me as capable as you.

147
00:08:28.000 --> 00:08:28.980
Give it back.

148
00:08:29.640 --> 00:08:30.840
I'm sorry.

149
00:08:40.409 --> 00:08:41.890
Did you want it that bad?

150
00:08:42.700 --> 00:08:43.610
Here.

151
00:08:49.290 --> 00:08:51.280
So you'll work harder.

152
00:08:51.550 --> 00:08:53.150
You still have much to learn.

153
00:08:57.520 --> 00:08:59.450
Come out. We have to go to the scene.

154
00:09:00.650 --> 00:09:01.490
Yes.

155
00:09:12.710 --> 00:09:13.760
Honey.

156
00:09:14.000 --> 00:09:15.460
-Honey!
-You can't enter.

157
00:09:15.620 --> 00:09:16.430
Please.

158
00:09:16.600 --> 00:09:17.690
Honey!

159
00:09:17.970 --> 00:09:19.800
Please let me in!

160
00:09:20.110 --> 00:09:22.330
I beg you. Please let me in.

161
00:09:22.490 --> 00:09:23.480
Detective!

162
00:09:23.930 --> 00:09:26.830
Please let me in. Please!

163
00:09:27.280 --> 00:09:30.400
Let me in. I have to see my husband!

164
00:09:34.100 --> 00:09:35.160
Name: Ahn Dongjin.

165
00:09:35.240 --> 00:09:36.660
Age: 37.

166
00:09:37.030 --> 00:09:39.040
His wife. Han Soojin.
who was asleep in the child's room.

167
00:09:39.040 --> 00:09:41.130
woke up when she
smelled something burning.

168
00:09:41.130 --> 00:09:44.090
She found her husband dead
in the master bedroom.

169
00:09:44.350 --> 00:09:47.080
So she rushed out with her child.

170
00:09:53.130 --> 00:09:53.970
Hello.

171
00:10:02.110 --> 00:10:03.640
What's the ignition point?

172
00:10:03.920 --> 00:10:06.320
A pot of boiling water
for instant noodles.

173
00:10:08.270 --> 00:10:11.360
He wanted to eat something to sober up.
and fell asleep.

174
00:10:11.790 --> 00:10:13.480
But you said he was found dead.

175
00:10:13.970 --> 00:10:14.820
Yes.

176
00:10:31.660 --> 00:10:34.020
The stabs were inflicted
at varying angles.

177
00:10:34.020 --> 00:10:35.550
and some stabs aren't deep.

178
00:10:35.630 --> 00:10:37.410
The assailant must have hesitated.

179
00:10:37.410 --> 00:10:39.530
Only when they made up their mind did they

180
00:10:39.530 --> 00:10:40.880
deliver the fatal strike.

181
00:10:40.880 --> 00:10:42.280
So. not a grudge killing.

182
00:10:42.430 --> 00:10:44.100
Likely someone close to him.

183
00:10:44.380 --> 00:10:45.280
Yes.

184
00:10:47.210 --> 00:10:49.030
It looks like he was sleeping.

185
00:10:49.180 --> 00:10:52.400
Maybe he was stabbed
while he was drunk.

186
00:10:52.550 --> 00:10:53.820
It's possible.

187
00:10:59.590 --> 00:11:00.300
Detective.

188
00:11:00.570 --> 00:11:01.430
Detective!

189
00:11:01.580 --> 00:11:03.700
Detective. please hear me out!

190
00:11:03.920 --> 00:11:05.050
It's Lee Hyunsoo.

191
00:11:05.190 --> 00:11:09.280
That criminal Lee Hyunsoo
stabbed my husband with a knife!

192
00:11:11.510 --> 00:11:13.300
It looks like he was sleeping.

193
00:11:15.110 --> 00:11:17.800
Please listen to me. Please...

194
00:11:20.470 --> 00:11:22.090
What are you doing? Keep up.

195
00:11:22.680 --> 00:11:23.820
Uh. yes.

196
00:11:30.940 --> 00:11:33.190
Lee Hyunsoo was
drinking with Ahn Dongjin until late.

197
00:11:33.190 --> 00:11:34.830
Could he be the murderer?

198
00:11:36.350 --> 00:11:39.260
Right now. he's one of the prime suspects.

199
00:11:39.580 --> 00:11:41.110
One of the suspects?

200
00:11:50.950 --> 00:11:52.120
Oh. this person?

201
00:11:52.210 --> 00:11:52.840
I know him.

202
00:11:52.990 --> 00:11:56.100
He brought a knife.
asking to blunt the tip of the blade.

203
00:11:56.680 --> 00:12:00.270
He's always been blunting knives
since he got out of prison.

204
00:12:06.040 --> 00:12:06.890
I don't know her.

205
00:12:06.890 --> 00:12:07.890
Who is she?

206
00:12:09.240 --> 00:12:12.410
I might've seen her around the area...

207
00:12:13.090 --> 00:12:15.210
Anyway. she never came here.

208
00:12:22.170 --> 00:12:23.160
Yes.

209
00:12:25.710 --> 00:12:26.800
OK.

210
00:12:27.380 --> 00:12:29.440
If you find anything. please call me.

211
00:12:36.010 --> 00:12:37.210
The autopsy results?

212
00:12:37.230 --> 00:12:37.960
Yes.

213
00:12:38.100 --> 00:12:40.310
The cause of death was hemorrhagic shock.

214
00:12:40.310 --> 00:12:42.240
According to the remnants of the bones.

215
00:12:42.240 --> 00:12:44.140
the tip of the knife is likely blunt.

216
00:12:44.140 --> 00:12:45.370
Lee Hyunsoo

217
00:12:45.580 --> 00:12:47.280
has a phobia of sharp objects.

218
00:12:47.460 --> 00:12:50.230
It's unlikely that
he'd use a sharpened blade.

219
00:12:50.690 --> 00:12:51.760
Yeah...

220
00:12:52.580 --> 00:12:55.090
Lee Hyunsoo's knife is a match. but...

221
00:12:55.390 --> 00:12:56.300
But?

222
00:12:57.490 --> 00:13:00.010
Ahn Dongjin's DNA was found
on Lee's knife.

223
00:13:00.330 --> 00:13:03.500
From the circumstantial evidence.
Lee's the culprit. but...

224
00:13:03.500 --> 00:13:04.550
But?

225
00:13:04.890 --> 00:13:07.580
Just now. you said Lee Hyunsoo is

226
00:13:07.820 --> 00:13:08.950
one of the suspects.

227
00:13:09.030 --> 00:13:10.070
And?

228
00:13:10.480 --> 00:13:13.200
You have other suspects in mind. right?

229
00:13:13.930 --> 00:13:15.740
Why beat around the bush?

230
00:13:16.310 --> 00:13:20.510
Didn't you show the shop owners
Han Soojin's photo because you suspect her?

231
00:13:29.660 --> 00:13:30.760
Yes.

232
00:13:31.480 --> 00:13:35.800
That criminal Lee Hyunsoo
stabbed my husband with a knife!

233
00:13:36.080 --> 00:13:37.840
She said Lee stabbed him.

234
00:13:38.440 --> 00:13:40.240
But Ahn Dongjin was under a blanket

235
00:13:40.240 --> 00:13:42.040
and looked like he was sleeping.

236
00:13:42.560 --> 00:13:44.840
While rushing out of the house.

237
00:13:44.990 --> 00:13:47.790
how did she know her husband
was stabbed to death?

238
00:13:48.860 --> 00:13:51.860
Something bugs me
about Lee Hyunsoo's statement too.

239
00:13:51.920 --> 00:13:54.720
Lee said that about a week
before Ahn Dongjin died.

240
00:13:54.800 --> 00:13:58.270
Ahn. his wife. and his son
visited his home with a watermelon.

241
00:13:58.710 --> 00:14:02.180
So she stole Lee Hyunsoo's knife then.

242
00:14:02.260 --> 00:14:03.990
and killed her husband with it?

243
00:14:04.070 --> 00:14:05.090
No.

244
00:14:05.390 --> 00:14:09.250
If that were the case. she would've had
no chance to put the knife back.

245
00:14:11.620 --> 00:14:12.620
Prosecutor Ju.

246
00:14:13.230 --> 00:14:14.170
Yeah?

247
00:14:14.880 --> 00:14:17.280
The murder of Granny Park with an awl.

248
00:14:17.630 --> 00:14:18.970
Why are you bringing that up?

249
00:14:18.970 --> 00:14:20.900
The murderer switched out the awl.

250
00:14:22.960 --> 00:14:24.260
So...

251
00:14:25.290 --> 00:14:26.660
in that visit.

252
00:14:26.800 --> 00:14:29.130
Han Soojin got Ahn's blood on Lee's knife.

253
00:14:29.510 --> 00:14:32.170
-Are you OK?
-The weapon that killed Ahn Dongjin

254
00:14:32.980 --> 00:14:35.040
is another knife that looks similar.

255
00:14:38.310 --> 00:14:39.160
Yes.

256
00:14:41.470 --> 00:14:43.760
This speculation is quite reasonable.

257
00:14:43.910 --> 00:14:45.830
But if we can't find evidence

258
00:14:45.990 --> 00:14:48.670
that she created a knife
like Lee Hyunsoo's.

259
00:14:49.000 --> 00:14:51.280
we have to prosecute Lee Hyunsoo.

260
00:14:51.700 --> 00:14:53.230
Speculations hold no value

261
00:14:53.250 --> 00:14:54.700
if there's no proof.

262
00:14:57.490 --> 00:14:59.450
[Hardware Store]

263
00:15:08.090 --> 00:15:09.210
It's closed.

264
00:15:09.680 --> 00:15:11.810
It's the last place we needed to check.

265
00:15:12.260 --> 00:15:14.590
Lee Hyunsoo might really be the culprit.

266
00:15:14.930 --> 00:15:17.270
What about Han Soojin's
credit card records?

267
00:15:17.270 --> 00:15:18.990
Mr. Song is still investigating.

268
00:15:18.990 --> 00:15:20.340
He hasn't called yet.

269
00:15:21.560 --> 00:15:22.890
What are you here to buy?

270
00:15:24.420 --> 00:15:25.250
Sir.

271
00:15:25.490 --> 00:15:27.320
do you do blade blunting?

272
00:15:28.690 --> 00:15:31.330
Is that the trend these days?

273
00:15:31.600 --> 00:15:34.230
Someone came to me with a photo too.

274
00:15:35.090 --> 00:15:38.300
Did someone else come to you
to blunt a blade?

275
00:15:38.750 --> 00:15:39.590
Yes.

276
00:15:39.800 --> 00:15:43.700
A pretty-looking lady
asked to blunt a knife's tip.

277
00:15:44.090 --> 00:15:45.880
I thought it was strange.

278
00:15:46.090 --> 00:15:49.450
but she said she was stabbed before
or something.

279
00:15:59.480 --> 00:16:00.830
Let me see...

280
00:16:03.640 --> 00:16:04.480
Sir.

281
00:16:04.950 --> 00:16:06.480
My goodness. You scared me!

282
00:16:06.740 --> 00:16:07.620
Does

283
00:16:08.780 --> 00:16:10.080
that work?

284
00:16:13.580 --> 00:16:15.560
[Prosecution]

285
00:16:24.390 --> 00:16:26.490
It is Han Soojin.

286
00:16:26.790 --> 00:16:28.380
Should we apply for an arrest warrant

287
00:16:28.380 --> 00:16:30.380
or request for witness attendance?

288
00:16:30.680 --> 00:16:33.280
Let's examine the crime scene
again tomorrow.

289
00:16:34.180 --> 00:16:36.370
Her face was caught on camera.
and we have

290
00:16:36.370 --> 00:16:38.340
the statement from
the hardware store's owner.

291
00:16:38.340 --> 00:16:40.740
so applying for a warrant
won't be an issue.

292
00:16:41.950 --> 00:16:42.940
Remember:

293
00:16:44.140 --> 00:16:45.040
we have to

294
00:16:45.220 --> 00:16:47.170
find the knife to win the trial.

295
00:16:47.450 --> 00:16:48.450
Yes.

296
00:16:52.040 --> 00:16:53.020
Lee Chaeha.

297
00:16:53.790 --> 00:16:54.720
Yes?

298
00:17:00.390 --> 00:17:01.830
It's Kim. the Koryoin.

299
00:17:06.250 --> 00:17:08.109
Get all the surveillance footage

300
00:17:08.220 --> 00:17:09.950
and see if there are witnesses.

301
00:17:11.069 --> 00:17:11.880
Yes.

302
00:17:25.079 --> 00:17:27.200
You're still here?

303
00:17:28.119 --> 00:17:29.140
Oh. yes.

304
00:17:29.510 --> 00:17:31.900
The witness interviews ran late.

305
00:17:32.070 --> 00:17:34.070
Are you two working overtime again?

306
00:17:34.510 --> 00:17:36.370
Have you even had dinner?

307
00:17:36.790 --> 00:17:38.270
Don't you need to rest?

308
00:17:38.390 --> 00:17:39.870
Let's clock out too.

309
00:17:40.130 --> 00:17:41.450
Oh! Wait for me!

310
00:17:42.510 --> 00:17:43.400
Mr. Lee.

311
00:17:43.480 --> 00:17:45.090
we're headed the same way anyway.

312
00:17:45.090 --> 00:17:45.910
Yes.

313
00:17:46.070 --> 00:17:48.740
No. he's coming with me.

314
00:17:50.660 --> 00:17:52.210
Are you going somewhere again?

315
00:17:52.210 --> 00:17:53.570
We're hungry.

316
00:17:53.810 --> 00:17:54.950
We'll get some food.

317
00:17:56.310 --> 00:17:57.190
Mr. Song can join...

318
00:17:57.190 --> 00:17:58.220
Get home safely.

319
00:17:58.770 --> 00:18:00.300
See you tomorrow. Mr. Song.

320
00:18:03.430 --> 00:18:04.340
OK.

321
00:18:08.330 --> 00:18:09.780
See you tomorrow!

322
00:18:15.330 --> 00:18:17.130
From now on. don't trust anyone.

323
00:18:17.270 --> 00:18:18.300
except me.

324
00:18:18.810 --> 00:18:19.620
OK.

325
00:18:19.800 --> 00:18:21.280
I'm hungry. Let's go.

326
00:18:24.530 --> 00:18:26.520
-Ma'am.
-One soju. please.

327
00:18:27.300 --> 00:18:28.130
Here you go.

328
00:18:28.250 --> 00:18:29.310
-Thank you.
-Sure.

329
00:18:29.670 --> 00:18:30.590
Yes. coming.

330
00:18:31.050 --> 00:18:31.720
Yes.

331
00:18:32.430 --> 00:18:33.330
I'm sorry.

332
00:18:44.730 --> 00:18:46.430
It's weirder if you pull away.

333
00:18:47.150 --> 00:18:48.090
Sorry?

334
00:18:48.510 --> 00:18:51.020
You pull away whenever we touch.

335
00:18:51.670 --> 00:18:53.710
It makes me more conscious about it.

336
00:18:56.650 --> 00:18:58.580
I wasn't thinking anything weird.

337
00:19:00.560 --> 00:19:01.640
Bottoms up.

338
00:19:01.940 --> 00:19:03.800
Let's drink when the food comes.

339
00:19:04.040 --> 00:19:06.300
You get drunk faster on an empty stomach.

340
00:19:06.310 --> 00:19:08.300
You must think my office is so laid-back

341
00:19:08.300 --> 00:19:10.400
that you can sit around

342
00:19:10.650 --> 00:19:11.600
getting drunk.

343
00:19:11.760 --> 00:19:12.710
Bottoms up.

344
00:19:17.810 --> 00:19:18.670
Bottoms up.

345
00:19:21.780 --> 00:19:22.580
Bottoms up.

346
00:19:27.540 --> 00:19:28.460
Bottoms up.

347
00:19:39.400 --> 00:19:40.250
Bottoms up.

348
00:19:40.640 --> 00:19:42.140
Prosecutor Ju.

349
00:19:43.200 --> 00:19:45.440
I really can't drink anymore.

350
00:19:45.610 --> 00:19:47.790
It's not a request but a command.

351
00:20:02.260 --> 00:20:03.380
Are you drunk?

352
00:20:03.660 --> 00:20:04.830
Yes.

353
00:20:05.110 --> 00:20:07.310
I'm so wasted.

354
00:20:09.950 --> 00:20:13.600
Your mother doesn't seem to be around too.

355
00:20:14.600 --> 00:20:18.410
Did you live with your uncle
since you were little?

356
00:20:19.080 --> 00:20:20.010
What?

357
00:20:20.880 --> 00:20:23.250
How did you know I don't have a mother?

358
00:20:24.220 --> 00:20:25.940
Prosecutor Ju.

359
00:20:26.060 --> 00:20:28.300
it's illegal to monitor civilians.

360
00:20:28.560 --> 00:20:29.600
you know?

361
00:20:30.280 --> 00:20:32.210
Stop messing around and answer me.

362
00:20:32.690 --> 00:20:34.750
You talk a lot for someone on thin ice.

363
00:20:36.200 --> 00:20:38.010
Hey. my carrot...

364
00:20:45.000 --> 00:20:47.430
I lived in my uncle's house.

365
00:20:48.720 --> 00:20:51.680
I enrolled in the Police University
to escape.

366
00:20:52.090 --> 00:20:55.570
Dorms are provided. and tuition is cheap.

367
00:21:03.700 --> 00:21:05.810
When you're drunk...

368
00:21:11.170 --> 00:21:12.540
you're so silly.

369
00:21:16.950 --> 00:21:19.030
I'm going home.

370
00:21:20.250 --> 00:21:22.070
I have work tomorrow.

371
00:21:25.160 --> 00:21:26.100
My carrots!

372
00:21:26.510 --> 00:21:27.460
Carrots.

373
00:21:32.940 --> 00:21:34.630
What the hell?

374
00:21:35.130 --> 00:21:36.760
Let go of me...

375
00:21:37.350 --> 00:21:39.890
Or I'll get told off again.

376
00:21:40.180 --> 00:21:42.390
Besides me. who else will tell you off?

377
00:21:42.540 --> 00:21:43.930
The Finger Cone.

378
00:21:44.360 --> 00:21:45.820
What? Finger Cone?

379
00:21:46.480 --> 00:21:48.800
Ju Taeseon!

380
00:21:51.890 --> 00:21:52.830
Oh?

381
00:21:53.280 --> 00:21:54.650
It's the Finger Cone!

382
00:21:55.010 --> 00:21:57.320
What are you doing here. Prosecutor Ju?

383
00:22:05.760 --> 00:22:06.810
Go inside.

384
00:22:15.030 --> 00:22:15.620
What?

385
00:22:15.810 --> 00:22:16.610
What's wrong?

386
00:22:34.490 --> 00:22:35.790
Lee Chaeha.

387
00:22:38.310 --> 00:22:39.880
You started it.

388
00:23:47.010 --> 00:23:47.840
Turn around.

389
00:24:08.470 --> 00:24:10.670
Don't look at me. I don't want to see you.

390
00:24:18.960 --> 00:24:21.070
[The Prosecutor's Proposal]

391
00:24:21.100 --> 00:24:24.850
[In the Next Episode]

392
00:24:21.140 --> 00:24:23.450
He messed with someone important to me.

393
00:24:23.590 --> 00:24:25.510
so I'm going to pay him back.

394
00:24:25.610 --> 00:24:26.470
That's a first.

395
00:24:26.620 --> 00:24:28.750
You have someone important to you now?

396
00:24:29.190 --> 00:24:29.950
Are you OK?

397
00:24:30.180 --> 00:24:31.160
I'm so sorry!

398
00:24:31.660 --> 00:24:33.320
How do you want to handle this?

399
00:24:33.530 --> 00:24:34.990
Have you thought about it?

400
00:24:35.160 --> 00:24:37.440
I was drunk and lost control.

401
00:24:37.450 --> 00:24:38.820
I meant every second of it.

402
00:24:38.820 --> 00:24:39.490
What?

403
00:24:39.640 --> 00:24:41.170
Why are you so out of breath?

404
00:24:41.560 --> 00:24:43.780
What. need help building your stamina?

405
00:24:43.890 --> 00:24:47.290
Seeing you like this
is getting me all hot and bothered again.

406
00:24:47.830 --> 00:24:48.960
What are you doing?

407
00:24:52.150 --> 00:24:53.810
Prosecutor Ju. move!
